==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|tūn||enclosure, village}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*tūną||fence}} (compare West Frisian {{term|tún|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|tuin||garden|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Zaun|lang=de}}, Danish/Swedish {{term|tun|lang=sv}}), from Gaulish {{term|dunon||hill, hillfort|lang=cel-gau}} (compare Welsh {{term|din||hill|lang=cy}}, Irish {{term|dún||fortress|lang=ga}}), from {{etyl|cel-pro|en}} {{m|cel-pro|*dūnom}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*dʰewh₂-||to finish, come full circle}}, (compare {{etyl|hit|-}} {{term|||it is finished|lang=hit|tr=tuhhušta|sc=Xsux}}, Latin {{m|la|fūnus||burial}}, Ancient Greek {{term|θνητός|tr=thnētos||mortal|lang=grc}}, {{term|θάνατος|tr=thanatos||death|lang=grc}}, {{term|||to die|tr=thaneīn|lang=grc|sc=Grek}}, Sanskrit {{term|||he vanished|lang=sa|tr=ádhvanīt|sc=Deva}}).

